  "Under 50/30/20, wants receive 30% of income: $5,200 times 0.30 equals $1,560. Marcus spends $1,800, so he overspends by $1,800 minus $1,560 equals $240 per month in the wants category.": "",
  "Priya has a $3,600/month income. Her fixed expenses are: rent $1,100, car payment $350, insurance $150, and student loan $280. What percentage of her income goes to fixed expenses, and does she have room for the recommended 20% savings?": "",
